        <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
            <head id="a4" altrender="biography">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
            <p>John R. Commons was born in Hollansburg, Ohio, October 13, 1862, he died May 11,
                1945. </p>
            <p>After graduating from Oberlin College, Commons earned his PhD at Johns Hopkins
                University. After appointments at Oberlin and Indiana University, he began teaching
                at Syracuse University. He was dismissed from Syracuse in 1899, after being
                considered a radical. </p>
            <p>Commons' early work exemplified his desire to unite Christian ideals with the
                emerging social sciences of sociology and economics. </p>
            <p>Common's contribution to labor history is considered equal to his contibutions to the
                theory of institutional economics.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
            <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
            <p>Reels 1-5 -- General correspondence, 1859, 1894-1967 </p>
            <p>Reels 6-8 -- Unemployment insurance for the Chicago Clothing Market, 1922-1929 </p>
            <p>Reels 9-11 -- Research files, 1875-1932 </p>
            <p>Reels 12-14 -- Book Manuscripts </p>
            <p>Reels 15-17 -- Articles, speeches, and miscellaneous writings, chronological file,
                scrapbooks, 1887-1918, 1938-1943 </p>
            <p>Reels 17-18 -- Unbound, 1908-1933 </p>
            <p>Reels 19-21 -- Topical file, 1892-1938. Reels 21-22 -- Newspaper clippings, 1906-1936 </p>
            <p>Reels 22-24 -- University file, 1910-1967 </p>
            <p>Reels 24 -- Photographs, 1881-1934</p>
        </scopecontent>
